"Terrazas-Mendoza L., Nikolskii-Gavrilov I., Herrera-Gómez S.S., Castillo-Álvarez M., Exebio-García A.A.","Alteration of soil fertility and irrigated maize and wheat vulnerability due to climate change [Alteración de la fertilidad del suelo, y vulnerabilidad de maíz y trigo bajo riego debido al cambio climático]",2010,"Tecnologia y Ciencias del Agua","1","1",,"87","102",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-84880310015&partnerID=40&md5=5591bd4773445c7f4906e4055d555e87","Colegio de Postgraduados, Programa de Hidrociencias, de la carretera México-Texcoco, 56230 Montecillos, Estado de México, Mexico; Universidad Autónoma Chapingo, Centro Regional Universitario Sureste, Carretera Teapa-Vicente Guerrero, Puyacatengo 86800 Teapa, Tabasco, Mexico","Terrazas-Mendoza, L., Colegio de Postgraduados, Programa de Hidrociencias, de la carretera México-Texcoco, 56230 Montecillos, Estado de México, Mexico; Nikolskii-Gavrilov, I., Colegio de Postgraduados, Programa de Hidrociencias, de la carretera México-Texcoco, 56230 Montecillos, Estado de México, Mexico; Herrera-Gómez, S.S., Colegio de Postgraduados, Programa de Hidrociencias, de la carretera México-Texcoco, 56230 Montecillos, Estado de México, Mexico; Castillo-Álvarez, M., Universidad Autónoma Chapingo, Centro Regional Universitario Sureste, Carretera Teapa-Vicente Guerrero, Puyacatengo 86800 Teapa, Tabasco, Mexico; Exebio-García, A.A., Colegio de Postgraduados, Programa de Hidrociencias, de la carretera México-Texcoco, 56230 Montecillos, Estado de México, Mexico","Estimation of agricultural crop vulnerability to global climate change has usually been made for rainfed crops without taking into account soil fertility alteration as a result of climate change. The main objective of this paper is to assess the role of the integrated soil fertility index modification in calculations of maize and wheat grain productivity in various irrigation districts in Mexico. The methodology to predict the alteration of some irrigated soil properties and integrated fertility index due to climate change has been developed. The results show that in Mexico, irrigated soil is less sensitive to climate change than rainfed agricultural soil and non-agricultural (virgin) soils, and it does not affect irrigated crop vulnerability to climate change significantly. The main effect of soil fertility alteration in estimations of irrigated crop vulnerability is expected in semiarid, semi-humid and humid tropical Mexican zones, where dimensionless mean annual radiative index of dryness IHT is less than 2.5.","Climatic index; Geographic law of soil zonality; Integrated soil fertility index",,,,,,,"Acock, B., Effects of carb on dioxide on photosyn (1990) Proceedings of A Symposium, (53), pp. 45-60. , thesis, plant growth, and other processes. In: Impact of carbon dioxide, trace gases, and climate change on global agriculture Kimball, B. A. (editor). IIASA, Special Publ; Allen, L., Plant responses to rising carbon dioxide and potential interactions with air pollutants (1990) Journal of Environmental Quality, 19, pp. 15-34; Ángeles, V., (2000) Diseñ O Agronómico de Sistemas de Riego Presurizado, p. 167. , Chapingo, Mé xico: Ed. UACh; Arnold, R., Szabolcs, I., Targulian, V., Global Soil Change (1990) Viena: Publ. IIASA, p. 109; Bazzaz, F., Sombroek, W., Global Climate Change and Agricultural Production Direct and Indirect Effects of Changing Hydrological (1996) Pedological and Plant Physiological Processes, p. 146. , Rome FAO Publ; Budyko, M., Climate and life (1974) Publ. Acad Emic, p. 508. , New York Press; Castillo, A.M., Nikolskii, I., Ortiz, C., Vaquera, H., Cruz, G., Mejía, E., González, A., Alteración de la fertilidad del suelo por el cambio climá tico y su efecto en la productividad agrícola (2007) Interciencia, 32 (6), pp. 368-376. , junio de; CONAGUA. Estadísticas agrícolas de los distritos de riego (2007) Anual de la CONAGUA Del 1990 Al 2006, , México D.F.: Comisión Nacional del Agua (informes impre